STATE
v.
OGLE 2018-0970 Supreme Court of Ohio. October 10, 2018

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

APPEALS NOT ACCEPTED FOR REVIEW Appellant's motion for order to strike, motion for leave to file amended notice of appeal, and motion for leave to file amended memorandum in support of jurisdiction denied. O'Donnell, Fischer, and DeGenaro, JJ., would grant appellant's motions for leave. DeWine, J., would grant appellant's motion for order to strike. Kennedy, J., would deny all of appellant's motions as moot.
